  "prompt": "How can I prepare for GRE in 20 days?",
  "response": "Preparing for the GRE in just 20 days requires an intensive and focused approach. Here's a strategic plan:\n\nVerbal Reasoning:\n1. Study vocabulary\n- Learn 300-500 high-frequency GRE words\n- Use flashcards or apps like Magoosh\n- Focus on word roots and synonyms\n\n2. Practice reading comprehension\n- Read complex passages daily\n- Time yourself\n- Solve official GRE verbal practice questions\n\nQuantitative Reasoning:\n1. Review fundamental math concepts\n- Algebra\n- Geometry\n- Basic statistics\n- Use official GRE math guides\n\n2. Practice problem-solving\n- Do timed practice tests\n- Focus on your weak areas\n- Learn shortcut techniques\n\nAnalytical Writing:\n1. Understand essay structures\n- Issue task\n- Argument task\n- Practice writing timed essays\n\nStudy Schedule:\n- 3-4 hours of focused study daily\n- Take full-length practice tests weekly\n- Use official ETS practice materials\n- Use online resources and prep books\n\nAdditional Tips:\n- Get adequate sleep\n- Manage stress\n- Take regular breaks\n- Stay motivated\n\nRecommended Resources:\n- Official GRE Guide\n- Magoosh GRE Prep\n- Khan Academy\n- ETS Practice Tests",
